be.kdg.sa.services

Class LicensePlateServiceProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • be.kdg.sa.services.LicensePlateServiceProxy

  • public class LicensePlateServiceProxy
extends java.lang.Object
    Proxy that simulates access to a fictive licenseplate service

    This a very thin proxy, it does not return a DTO but plain JSON. Calling get(plateId) will return the following 

    
    {
         plateId: int, the id of the plate that was requested,
         nationalNumber: string, the national number of the owner of the vehicle,
         euroNumber: int, the euronorm of the vehicle
   }
    This proxy is meant for testing purposes and has limited functionality
    • no real HTTP call is made; the proxy only holds the calling thread for 200 ms to simulate network latency
    • plateId's are supposed to be 9 chars long but no further checks are done
    • plateId's 1-ABC-123 to 4-ABC-123 return fixed data
    • all other valid plateId return random data (different on each call)
    • plateId 1-ERR-123 will raise an IOException to simulate a communication error
    • plateId 1-UNK-123 will raise a LicensePlateNotFoundException

        Mimics a get for a single licenseplate resource on a remote HTTP service using the supplied id.
        Parameters:
        plateId - a vald license plate
        Returns:
        a response in the correct JSON format (see class documentation)
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there is a communication/service failure
        InvalidLicensePlateException - if the plate contains no 9 chars (no other checks are done for the moment)
        LicensePlateNotFoundException - if there is no plate with the supplied id
